      • putNormalizedAttribute

        protected final void putNormalizedAttribute(java.lang.String key,
                                            java.lang.Object value)
        Stash an attribute that may be normalized at this level. In other words, an attribute that may have been pulled up from the child elements because its value was the same in all children.

        Stashing an attribute allows child element parsers to retrieve the values of normalized attributes using getNormalizedAttribute(String).

        Parameters:
        key - The name of the attribute.
        value - The value of the attribute.

      • getNormalizedAttribute

        protected final java.lang.Object getNormalizedAttribute(java.lang.String key)
        Attempt to retrieve a stashed normalized attribute. If there is no stashed attribute with the provided name, the parent element parser will be queried, and so on up the chain.
        Parameters:
        key - The name of the attribute.
        Returns:
        The stashed value, or null if the attribute was not be found.
